<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The destination (header_malloced) is allocated with header_len+1 bytes so the write is safe, but the source (header) is not validated. If header is NULL or points to an object smaller than header_len (e.g. a shorter string or incorrectly computed length), then memcpy(header_malloced, header, header_len) will read beyond the bounds of the source object, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
